1
00:00:21,564 --> 00:00:23,023
Don't call me your son.

2
00:00:23,107 --> 00:00:26,318
<i>A lot of bad things happened</i>
<i>in my life, Teo.</i>

3
00:00:26,402 --> 00:00:29,488
I had no idea they were a syndicate.

4
00:00:29,572 --> 00:00:32,158
I don't even know
if I can still believe you.

5
00:00:32,241 --> 00:00:34,034
<i>Why didn't you tell me</i>
<i>that my mother was alive?</i>

6
00:00:34,118 --> 00:00:36,954
Your mother is involved
in the illegal business of the Veronas.

7
00:00:37,037 --> 00:00:38,205
<i>You would've been in danger.</i>

8
00:00:38,289 --> 00:00:39,957
- Who are you?
- Well, who are you?

9
00:00:40,040 --> 00:00:42,501
Do you know Yana and Teo?
Tell me where they're hiding.

10
00:00:42,585 --> 00:00:44,170
Send me the ten million pesos.

11
00:00:45,880 --> 00:00:47,715
<i>You really have no shame.</i>

12
00:00:47,798 --> 00:00:49,383
You are no longer hiding.

13
00:00:49,467 --> 00:00:51,051
Because he chose me.

14
00:00:51,802 --> 00:00:53,846
<i>Pa, that Pearl is here.</i>

15
00:00:53,929 --> 00:00:55,890
Jorge and your mistress know each other?

16
00:00:55,973 --> 00:00:57,725
Stay put. I'll deal with it.

17
00:01:01,812 --> 00:01:06,025
♪ <i>Love is never gone... ♪</i>

18
00:01:41,435 --> 00:01:42,520
It's over.

19
00:01:43,145 --> 00:01:44,313
It's over?

20
00:01:44,814 --> 00:01:45,940
Yes.

21
00:01:47,650 --> 00:01:50,152
- She's gone.
- Just like that?

22
00:01:50,861 --> 00:01:51,946
It's done?

23
00:01:52,655 --> 00:01:53,489
That's it?

24
00:01:59,203 --> 00:02:01,455
What more do you want, Katarina?

25
00:02:09,171 --> 00:02:12,258
I want you to beg and grovel at my feet.

26
00:02:13,592 --> 00:02:16,387
I want you to go to hell
the same way she did.

27
00:02:16,470 --> 00:02:18,389
What's done is done.

28
00:02:18,973 --> 00:02:20,891
- Yeah, yeah, yeah.
- An ending is an ending.

29
00:02:34,238 --> 00:02:35,823
This is what I like about you.

30
00:02:35,906 --> 00:02:39,159
You are truly a man of strength.

31
00:02:42,454 --> 00:02:44,540
A man of pure strength.

32
00:02:45,624 --> 00:02:48,836
Thank you so much
for that wonderful ending.

33
00:02:49,712 --> 00:02:51,046
You're welcome.

34
00:02:58,220 --> 00:02:59,388
To new beginnings.

35
00:03:16,238 --> 00:03:18,365


36
00:03:18,449 --> 00:03:20,868


37
00:03:22,244 --> 00:03:24,163
-
Hey!

38
00:03:26,707 --> 00:03:28,959


39
00:03:34,340 --> 00:03:36,175
- Boss, we have to go!
Leave that! Let's go!

40
00:03:37,509 --> 00:03:38,594
Come on!

41
00:03:53,400 --> 00:03:54,485
Ma?

42
00:03:54,568 --> 00:03:56,570


43
00:03:57,446 --> 00:03:59,114
Ma. Ma.

44
00:04:00,366 --> 00:04:01,367
Ma.

45
00:04:03,661 --> 00:04:04,662
Ma!

46
00:04:11,961 --> 00:04:13,337


47
00:04:13,420 --> 00:04:14,755
Ma, it's me.

48
00:04:15,673 --> 00:04:17,257
- Come on.

49
00:04:33,148 --> 00:04:35,067
Feeling the remorse yet?

50
00:04:35,484 --> 00:04:36,652
Any regrets?

51
00:04:38,153 --> 00:04:41,073
I know this is hard on you, Pa.
You trusted Pearl.

52
00:04:41,156 --> 00:04:43,242
But now you know
how I feel towards Gem now.

53
00:04:43,325 --> 00:04:45,119
I don't want to talk about it.

54
00:04:46,662 --> 00:04:48,998

Where did you take Pearl's body?

55
00:04:50,040 --> 00:04:52,793
There was
a complicated situation last night, Pa.

56
00:04:52,876 --> 00:04:56,588
I only got Jorge's body.
I couldn't get Pearl's.

57
00:04:56,672 --> 00:04:57,715
What?

58
00:04:57,798 --> 00:04:59,425
Well, she's dead anyway, right?

59
00:04:59,508 --> 00:05:01,844
You left Pearl's corpse?

60
00:05:02,553 --> 00:05:04,471
I wanted her burned, Ace!

61
00:05:05,014 --> 00:05:08,851
I wanted her body turned into ashes
and thrown into the sewer!

62
00:05:08,934 --> 00:05:11,603
Her family can't find her!

63
00:05:11,687 --> 00:05:14,773
She doesn't deserve a grave,
much less a prayer!

64
00:05:14,857 --> 00:05:16,608
They won't even dare to report it.

65
00:05:16,692 --> 00:05:18,318
What do you think
they would say to the police?

66
00:05:18,402 --> 00:05:20,070
That their mother,
mistress of a judge

67
00:05:20,154 --> 00:05:22,156
running a human smuggling ring,
was shot to death?

68
00:05:22,239 --> 00:05:23,782
They will just hide her
to protect themselves.

69
00:05:24,783 --> 00:05:27,119
You're gambling on their silence!

70
00:05:27,202 --> 00:05:30,205
What if they use the body
to pin the blame on us?

71
00:05:30,998 --> 00:05:34,418

Ace, you don't leave loose ends!

72
00:05:34,501 --> 00:05:35,753
Why?

73
00:05:35,836 --> 00:05:37,921

You really want to have her corpse?

74
00:05:38,005 --> 00:05:40,591
For what?
So you could hug someone at night?

75
00:05:40,674 --> 00:05:42,342
You're talking
about loose ends, but the truth is,

76
00:05:42,426 --> 00:05:44,762
you're going crazy over the fact
that you didn't get to say goodbye.

77
00:05:44,845 --> 00:05:48,098
- Watch your words!
Stop the remorse, Pa!

78
00:05:48,974 --> 00:05:50,225
You killed her, right?

79
00:05:50,934 --> 00:05:52,561
Then own up to it.

80
00:05:52,644 --> 00:05:53,562
Leave Pearl to the maggots,

81
00:05:53,645 --> 00:05:55,230
and let's focus on better things
right now.

82
00:05:55,314 --> 00:05:57,149

Like rescuing my child and Gem.

83
00:05:57,649 --> 00:05:59,401
That's the only blood
that matters right now.

84
00:06:08,660 --> 00:06:10,829
Why did you bring her here?

85
00:06:11,955 --> 00:06:14,541
- Ma, I brought you some food.
She has nowhere to go.

86
00:06:14,625 --> 00:06:16,043
Divino's going to kill her.

87
00:06:16,126 --> 00:06:19,546
I don't care! I don't want her here!

88
00:06:19,630 --> 00:06:21,048
Where will I take her?

89
00:06:21,131 --> 00:06:23,509
To hell! Anywhere! Just not here!

90
00:06:24,301 --> 00:06:25,511
Pa!

91
00:06:28,847 --> 00:06:30,182
- Pa...
Pa!

92
00:06:35,312 --> 00:06:38,190
You have no shame, showing your face here.

93
00:06:39,525 --> 00:06:40,651
You're not welcome here.

94
00:06:42,027 --> 00:06:43,946
What do you think of our house?

95
00:06:45,114 --> 00:06:47,116
A garbage bin
where you can dump your mistakes?

96
00:06:47,866 --> 00:06:51,870
You're not getting any pity from me,
so you'd better recover quickly.

97
00:06:51,954 --> 00:06:55,958
I don't want you stinking up this place
with your presence.

98
00:06:56,416 --> 00:06:58,418
Leave when you can...

99
00:06:58,502 --> 00:07:00,546
- Teo...
...or I might just finish

100
00:07:00,629 --> 00:07:03,549
what Divino could not!

101
00:07:05,092 --> 00:07:06,343
Pa, that's enough.

102
00:07:08,595 --> 00:07:09,680
That's enough.

103
00:07:14,351 --> 00:07:15,269


104
00:07:15,352 --> 00:07:16,645
Good afternoon, madam.

105
00:07:16,728 --> 00:07:19,022
A good afternoon, indeed.

106
00:07:19,106 --> 00:07:21,108
And I have you to thank for it.

107
00:07:22,317 --> 00:07:24,987
Thank you, Larajean.
You've proven your worth.

108
00:07:25,654 --> 00:07:26,655
Uh...

109
00:07:27,406 --> 00:07:29,241
What happened, madam?

110
00:07:29,324 --> 00:07:34,163
Well,
Rita Crisanto, AKA Pearl,

111
00:07:34,746 --> 00:07:36,832
my husband's mistress...

112
00:07:36,915 --> 00:07:39,501
is now dead.

113
00:07:39,585 --> 00:07:41,795


114
00:07:41,879 --> 00:07:44,089
Thank you for your information.

115
00:07:44,173 --> 00:07:46,133

We've pulled the weed from our midst.

116
00:07:46,925 --> 00:07:50,012
And because of that,
your loyalty will be rewarded.

117
00:07:50,095 --> 00:07:52,055
Oh, but of course!

118
00:07:52,139 --> 00:07:53,974
Ace, you take care of it.

119
00:07:54,474 --> 00:07:55,559
Yes, Ma.

120
00:07:58,103 --> 00:07:59,188
But...

121
00:07:59,688 --> 00:08:03,358
I-I didn't want that--
I didn't want that to h-happen.

122
00:08:03,442 --> 00:08:05,652
Well, that's what we wanted.

123
00:08:06,320 --> 00:08:09,489
A-and I didn't... I didn't...

124
00:08:10,407 --> 00:08:12,326
I didn't think you were going to kill her.

125
00:08:12,409 --> 00:08:14,411
Are you sure it was her?

126
00:08:14,494 --> 00:08:15,913
Yes. Confirmed.

127
00:08:16,455 --> 00:08:18,540
I saw her with my own eyes.

128
00:08:18,624 --> 00:08:20,375
She deserved it, anyway.

129
00:08:23,754 --> 00:08:25,756
- Mary?
- Yes, sir?

130
00:08:35,057 --> 00:08:37,392
Here. Your reward.

131
00:08:37,476 --> 00:08:38,685
Um...

132
00:08:40,812 --> 00:08:42,064
You don't want it?

133
00:08:55,702 --> 00:08:57,454
Sir, sorry.

134
00:09:00,374 --> 00:09:01,500
Sorry because...

135
00:09:03,293 --> 00:09:05,295
your wife loves someone else.

136
00:09:07,589 --> 00:09:08,674
I feel sorry for you too.

137
00:09:08,757 --> 00:09:11,885
The man you're obsessed with
is also in love with someone else.

138
00:09:13,553 --> 00:09:16,890
After so long, my feelings
seem to have passed too.

139
00:09:18,725 --> 00:09:20,310
Stop denying.

140
00:09:20,394 --> 00:09:22,437
Just accept it what it is.

141
00:09:22,521 --> 00:09:24,815
That's the first step
for you to forget about Teo.

142
00:09:25,357 --> 00:09:27,526
But it's not easy to just forget someone.

143
00:09:28,735 --> 00:09:29,987
How about you?

144
00:09:30,070 --> 00:09:32,155
Have you forgotten about Ma'am Gem yet?

145
00:09:32,698 --> 00:09:35,284
Can you even forget her?

146
00:09:35,367 --> 00:09:38,620
Gem is my wife. She's mine.

147
00:09:39,288 --> 00:09:42,374
What does Teo even have
that makes you two crazy for him?

148
00:09:43,041 --> 00:09:44,042
I don't know.

149
00:09:45,460 --> 00:09:48,463
We've given them our everything.

150
00:09:49,298 --> 00:09:51,967
But why didn't they choose us?

151
00:09:52,426 --> 00:09:53,677
Because they're stupid.

152
00:09:56,263 --> 00:09:57,431
Stupid idiots.

153
00:09:58,348 --> 00:09:59,599
You're right.

154
00:10:00,600 --> 00:10:04,354
That's why we shouldn't
waste our tears on them.

155
00:10:04,438 --> 00:10:08,191
Actually, we should be drunk on happiness.

156
00:10:18,201 --> 00:10:21,121
Fill it up.

157
00:10:21,747 --> 00:10:23,999
Okay.
There you go, there you go.

158
00:10:26,960 --> 00:10:30,630
We deserve to be happy,
just for tonight.

159
00:11:21,014 --> 00:11:25,185
<i>A body was found</i>
<i>right here on this vacant lot.</i>

160
00:11:25,268 --> 00:11:29,189
<i>The police confirmed</i>
<i>that it is Jorge Ybañez,</i>

161
00:11:29,272 --> 00:11:32,776
<i>father of Gem Verona,</i>
<i>who is also currently missing.</i>

162
00:11:32,859 --> 00:11:35,862
<i>As of now, the Verona family</i>
<i>has not made any statement</i>

163
00:11:35,946 --> 00:11:39,032
<i>regarding the vile murder of their in-law.</i>

164
00:11:45,080 --> 00:11:47,999
Even if we're not really related...

165
00:11:49,793 --> 00:11:53,213
Even though it was fake,
he was still like a father to me.

166
00:11:56,800 --> 00:11:59,469
I asked you to do one thing!

167
00:12:00,679 --> 00:12:03,098
I told you to keep things clean!

168
00:12:03,181 --> 00:12:04,599
He was identified!

169
00:12:05,058 --> 00:12:08,228
What if they find out Jorge's real name?

170
00:12:08,311 --> 00:12:10,021
His identity
was just made up by your wife,

171
00:12:10,105 --> 00:12:12,941
who you are trying to protect,
even after she deceived us?

172
00:12:13,024 --> 00:12:14,943
I told Elmer and the others
to make it clean!

173
00:12:15,861 --> 00:12:17,863
I'll punish them, for real.

174
00:12:18,613 --> 00:12:20,699
It's too late for that now!

175
00:12:20,782 --> 00:12:22,534
I should've done it myself!

176
00:12:22,617 --> 00:12:24,494
You are so incompetent!

177
00:12:25,537 --> 00:12:28,290
You even let them take away Pearl's body!

178
00:12:28,373 --> 00:12:29,499
There it is!

179
00:12:29,583 --> 00:12:31,835
That's why you're mad, right?
It's all about Pearl!

180
00:12:32,836 --> 00:12:35,088
Why are you so upset with me
when this is also your fault?

181
00:12:35,714 --> 00:12:37,340
Huge mistake, Pa.

182
00:12:37,424 --> 00:12:38,467
We're all the same here!

183
00:12:38,550 --> 00:12:39,926
We are not the same!

184
00:12:40,010 --> 00:12:42,137
I am using my brain, but you--

185
00:12:42,220 --> 00:12:43,638
What about me?

186
00:12:43,722 --> 00:12:44,806
You think I'm crazy?

187
00:12:46,141 --> 00:12:48,143
We're all crazy in this household!

188
00:12:48,226 --> 00:12:50,812
How dare you speak to me that way, huh?

189
00:12:50,896 --> 00:12:52,147
Who do you think you are?

190
00:12:52,230 --> 00:12:53,732
- Who do you think you are?
- Pa! Stop!

191
00:12:53,815 --> 00:12:56,193
- Pa! Ma!
- You never learned your lessons!

192
00:12:56,276 --> 00:12:57,777
- What's going on?
- When will you think?

193
00:12:57,861 --> 00:13:00,113
- When will you ever learn?
- Stop it, Pa!

194
00:13:00,197 --> 00:13:02,699
- You never, ever even learn your lesson!
- Divino, stop! Stop it!

195
00:13:03,783 --> 00:13:05,035
Stop it, Ace! Stop!

196
00:13:06,203 --> 00:13:07,412
Ace, no!

197
00:13:07,496 --> 00:13:09,664
Divino--

198
00:13:09,748 --> 00:13:11,082
Stop! Stop it, please!

199
00:13:11,166 --> 00:13:13,210
You don't call the shots here!

200
00:13:13,919 --> 00:13:17,088
Stop it. Stop it. Enough!

201
00:13:17,589 --> 00:13:20,175
Come on. Come here.
Come here, Ace.

202
00:13:20,258 --> 00:13:21,968
Leave me!

203
00:13:22,677 --> 00:13:25,597
What happened?

204
00:13:26,723 --> 00:13:28,391
You're evil!

205
00:13:29,226 --> 00:13:31,061
You're so evil!

206
00:13:31,811 --> 00:13:33,063
Did you just find that out?

207
00:13:33,688 --> 00:13:35,190
Ace, please.

208
00:13:37,400 --> 00:13:39,569
- Sir, are you--
- Get off me!

209
00:13:44,032 --> 00:13:46,117
Dear, are you okay?

210
00:13:55,252 --> 00:13:57,420
Wherever you go...

211
00:13:58,672 --> 00:14:00,924
death follows you.

212
00:14:02,425 --> 00:14:04,177
So, what's your decision?

213
00:14:04,261 --> 00:14:05,762
Where are you planning to go?

214
00:14:06,680 --> 00:14:09,432
Pa, we are leaving together.

215
00:14:13,395 --> 00:14:15,313
How can I help?

216
00:14:15,397 --> 00:14:17,607
I still have some money saved up.

217
00:14:18,191 --> 00:14:21,695
Just keep it.
We still have some funds left.

218
00:14:21,778 --> 00:14:23,780
I'm not coming with you.

219
00:14:24,614 --> 00:14:29,119
When I'm strong enough,
I'll find a place I can hide in.

220
00:14:30,245 --> 00:14:32,080
About your plan...

221
00:14:32,747 --> 00:14:34,165
go ahead with it.

222
00:14:34,249 --> 00:14:35,834
Ma, no.

223
00:14:37,586 --> 00:14:40,422
Ma, you're coming with us.

224
00:14:41,881 --> 00:14:44,134
I got you a passport you can use.

225
00:14:44,676 --> 00:14:47,262
I can't, in good conscience,
just leave you here.

226
00:14:47,846 --> 00:14:49,681
We're all going to Vietnam.

227
00:14:50,432 --> 00:14:53,393
Vietnam... passport...

228
00:14:53,476 --> 00:14:54,936
Is that all?

229
00:14:55,437 --> 00:14:58,440
You're talking like
you're just planning a vacation

230
00:14:58,982 --> 00:15:01,568
while corpses
are turning up everywhere.

231
00:15:01,651 --> 00:15:04,821
Pa, this is the only way
I can keep us all safe.

232
00:15:06,448 --> 00:15:07,699
Safe?

233
00:15:13,538 --> 00:15:15,206
You're making it sound like...

234
00:15:17,459 --> 00:15:18,585
like I'm useless.

235
00:15:18,668 --> 00:15:19,753
What am I to you?

236
00:15:20,420 --> 00:15:22,422
Am I here just for decoration?

237
00:15:22,922 --> 00:15:25,925
Just because I'm lame
and I'm not earning money...

238
00:15:27,761 --> 00:15:30,847
does that mean I have no right
to decide where I want to die?

239
00:15:32,724 --> 00:15:34,726
I am the head of this family.

240
00:15:35,769 --> 00:15:37,187
But right now, I feel like...

241
00:15:37,854 --> 00:15:40,190
you're just dragging me
wherever you want to go.

242
00:15:40,982 --> 00:15:44,569
And I'm following your plans,
even though I'm not involved in them

243
00:15:44,653 --> 00:15:46,863
because you made them behind my back.

244
00:15:47,364 --> 00:15:48,406
Pa...

245
00:15:49,783 --> 00:15:52,619
Pa, it's for our sake too.

246
00:15:53,745 --> 00:15:54,913
Our sake?

247
00:15:56,498 --> 00:15:57,916
Or your sake?

248
00:15:57,999 --> 00:16:01,628
I'm so tired of following your plans

249
00:16:01,711 --> 00:16:03,546
that just lead to death.

250
00:16:03,963 --> 00:16:07,801
If you want me to come with you,
treat me like a human being.

251
00:16:07,884 --> 00:16:13,723
Don't treat me like baggage
you just drag everywhere!

252
00:16:55,640 --> 00:16:56,641
Hello?

253
00:16:56,725 --> 00:16:58,184
Divino.

254
00:17:01,146 --> 00:17:02,188
You're alive.

255
00:17:03,440 --> 00:17:05,525
<i>Yes, I'm still alive.</i>

256
00:17:05,608 --> 00:17:08,403
But I know
that's not what you want to hear.

257
00:17:09,154 --> 00:17:11,322
You have no idea.

258
00:17:12,282 --> 00:17:13,950
You're really persistent.

259
00:17:14,617 --> 00:17:17,537
<i>If you're going to kill me, do it.</i>

260
00:17:17,620 --> 00:17:19,164
<i>That is your right.</i>

261
00:17:19,247 --> 00:17:21,499
But please...

262
00:17:21,583 --> 00:17:23,168
<i>don't hurt my family.</i>

263
00:17:24,252 --> 00:17:28,923
Don't drag my family into this.
It's all my fault, anyway.

264
00:17:29,007 --> 00:17:30,592
Too late for that.

265
00:17:31,259 --> 00:17:33,762
I will never forgive you
for your betrayal, Pearl.

266
00:17:35,305 --> 00:17:37,056
I gave you everything!

267
00:17:37,140 --> 00:17:39,601
My trust, my protection...

268
00:17:40,643 --> 00:17:44,063
You deceived us in our own home!

269
00:17:45,190 --> 00:17:46,941
I'm sorry, Divino.

270
00:17:50,236 --> 00:17:51,404
Sorry.

271
00:17:51,863 --> 00:17:53,782
It doesn't matter!

272
00:17:54,616 --> 00:17:58,203
You stabbed me in the back
while we were together.

273
00:18:00,246 --> 00:18:01,414
Divino.

274
00:18:03,917 --> 00:18:05,168
Please.

275
00:18:06,920 --> 00:18:08,338
Not my family.

276
00:18:09,214 --> 00:18:10,632
<i>Don't drag them into this mess.</i>

277
00:18:11,174 --> 00:18:12,842
They know nothing about this.

278
00:18:13,551 --> 00:18:15,470
Teo, Gem...

279
00:18:15,553 --> 00:18:17,806
...let them live peacefully.

280
00:18:17,889 --> 00:18:22,977
There will be no peace
until everyone around you is dead!

281
00:18:23,520 --> 00:18:25,605
I'm going to kill you all!

282
00:18:25,688 --> 00:18:27,106
If that's the case,

283
00:18:27,982 --> 00:18:30,318
then we have nothing else to talk about.

284
00:18:30,902 --> 00:18:34,823
If you won't leave them alone,
I'll fight back, Divino.

285
00:18:35,740 --> 00:18:37,992
Until the last drop of my blood.

286
00:18:38,952 --> 00:18:41,538
I won't let you hurt them!

287
00:18:41,621 --> 00:18:42,872
Try me.

288
00:18:43,540 --> 00:18:47,460
Let's see how far a walking corpse can go!

289
00:18:53,341 --> 00:18:55,009
Oh, my goodness!

290
00:18:55,093 --> 00:18:57,554
So that woman is still alive and kicking?

291
00:18:58,304 --> 00:19:01,641
I can't believe
that we're still dealing with this woman!

292
00:19:11,943 --> 00:19:12,986
Sir.

293
00:19:13,444 --> 00:19:14,612
Sir, good morning.

294
00:19:15,905 --> 00:19:17,073
Good morning.

295
00:19:17,699 --> 00:19:18,616
Why are you here?

296
00:19:18,700 --> 00:19:21,452
Madam Katarina asked me to come here.

297
00:19:21,536 --> 00:19:23,621
She's working from home today.

298
00:19:23,705 --> 00:19:24,789
Me too.

299
00:19:26,958 --> 00:19:29,711
Sir, I heard about that...

300
00:19:29,794 --> 00:19:31,963
that fake father of Gem.

301
00:19:32,046 --> 00:19:33,923
He was found at a dumpsite.

302
00:19:34,799 --> 00:19:37,051
I just wanted to ask

303
00:19:37,135 --> 00:19:40,722
if Jorge's death had anything to do
with what happened with Miss Rita.

304
00:19:41,347 --> 00:19:45,518
I mean... I-I'm not saying
that you killed him too, but--

305
00:19:45,602 --> 00:19:48,396
Who said that Pearl is dead, hmm?

306
00:19:48,980 --> 00:19:50,899
That bitch is alive.

307
00:19:51,441 --> 00:19:53,276
She's staying with Teo right now.

308
00:19:53,985 --> 00:19:55,987
Bad weeds sure are hard to kill.

309
00:19:56,487 --> 00:19:59,699
Even after we showered her with bullets,
she still managed to escape.

310
00:20:00,283 --> 00:20:03,036
Next time, she won't be so lucky.

311
00:20:47,789 --> 00:20:49,040
- Let's go.
- Okay.

312
00:20:52,043 --> 00:20:53,628
Look, Issay!

313
00:20:53,711 --> 00:20:56,381
Who said you couldn't
celebrate your birthday?

314
00:20:56,464 --> 00:20:59,300
- We've got <i>pansit!</i>
- Chicken, too!

315
00:20:59,384 --> 00:21:02,387
And of course, <i>ensaymada</i> from downtown.

316
00:21:02,470 --> 00:21:04,347
Wow! Thank you!

317
00:21:04,430 --> 00:21:06,641
And we can't forget the cake!

318
00:21:06,724 --> 00:21:08,810
Happy birthday! Come on, make a wish.

319
00:21:08,893 --> 00:21:10,311
Make a wish, Issay.

320
00:21:11,104 --> 00:21:14,190
Teo, do birthday wishes come true?

321
00:21:14,273 --> 00:21:16,776
Who will make them happen?

322
00:21:18,945 --> 00:21:19,946
Papa!

323
00:21:21,823 --> 00:21:22,740
Papa.

324
00:21:24,826 --> 00:21:26,995
I want you to grant my wish.

325
00:21:27,078 --> 00:21:28,621
I wish...

326
00:21:28,705 --> 00:21:30,707
we could stay together as a family.

327
00:21:31,416 --> 00:21:35,253
I also wish
that we never have to leave Mama.

328
00:21:43,344 --> 00:21:44,846
Happy birthday, dear.

329
00:21:44,929 --> 00:21:46,097
Thank you, Papa.

330
00:21:47,473 --> 00:21:49,308
Go ahead and blow out your candle.

331
00:21:50,601 --> 00:21:51,978
Come here, Issay.

332
00:21:52,603 --> 00:21:56,107
I'm lighting the candle now,
so you can make your wish.

333
00:22:19,756 --> 00:22:21,674
Please forgive me, Alonzo.

334
00:22:22,675 --> 00:22:25,678
I'm sorry for the things I said before.

335
00:22:27,680 --> 00:22:29,015
Just stop, Rita.

336
00:22:31,142 --> 00:22:32,894
It's your daughter's birthday.

337
00:22:34,103 --> 00:22:37,273
Don't ruin it with your lies

338
00:22:37,356 --> 00:22:40,276
and your excuses
about why you didn't come back to us.

339
00:22:41,069 --> 00:22:43,654
You've already explained that
to me very clearly.

340
00:22:45,782 --> 00:22:47,200
No.

341
00:22:50,244 --> 00:22:53,331
There's something else
you need to know, Alonzo.

342
00:22:53,873 --> 00:22:55,124
I couldn't...

343
00:22:56,542 --> 00:22:58,294
tell you right away because...

344
00:23:01,005 --> 00:23:02,173
I knew...

345
00:23:06,385 --> 00:23:09,305
...you would be even less willing
to accept me.

346
00:23:11,390 --> 00:23:13,643
You keep talking too much.

347
00:23:15,645 --> 00:23:16,979
The truth is,

348
00:23:18,106 --> 00:23:20,316
you really didn't want to come back to us

349
00:23:20,399 --> 00:23:23,611
because you were fooling around
with another man.

350
00:23:27,865 --> 00:23:29,700
I suffered.

351
00:23:36,082 --> 00:23:38,334
I was raped.

352
00:23:42,547 --> 00:23:44,632
By multiple men.

353
00:23:48,678 --> 00:23:50,763
They passed me around.

354
00:23:55,059 --> 00:23:57,979
I was deceived by the recruiter.

355
00:24:00,106 --> 00:24:04,777
I ended up with demons
who took advantage of me.

356
00:24:07,864 --> 00:24:09,699
I tried many times...

357
00:24:10,408 --> 00:24:13,911
to escape, but I kept failing.

358
00:24:14,787 --> 00:24:17,874
I almost died several times.

359
00:24:18,374 --> 00:24:21,878
Eventually, I grew tired of fighting.

360
00:24:30,511 --> 00:24:32,763
I just endured everything.

361
00:24:34,557 --> 00:24:37,560
Because I no longer had
the strength to face you.

362
00:24:37,643 --> 00:24:40,146
Then I met Divino.

363
00:24:41,439 --> 00:24:43,191
He saved me.

364
00:24:43,274 --> 00:24:46,277
He pulled me out of that hell.

365
00:24:47,320 --> 00:24:48,988
Soon, we started a relationship.

366
00:24:50,323 --> 00:24:54,243
He did so much for me.

367
00:24:55,369 --> 00:24:57,538
Is that how you repay your debt?

368
00:24:59,081 --> 00:25:00,583
You know, Rita, if...

369
00:25:02,293 --> 00:25:06,005
if you really want my forgiveness,

370
00:25:06,464 --> 00:25:08,883
I'll give it to you.

371
00:25:08,966 --> 00:25:10,718
I forgive you.

372
00:25:13,679 --> 00:25:15,514
But I'm begging you.

373
00:25:17,600 --> 00:25:19,852
Please disappear from our lives.

374
00:25:20,269 --> 00:25:21,604
Just vanish.

375
00:25:23,314 --> 00:25:24,732
I'm pleading with you.

376
00:26:07,984 --> 00:26:10,236
I'll talk to Papa.

377
00:26:16,784 --> 00:26:19,537
I understand your father.

378
00:26:23,916 --> 00:26:25,751
Still, you went through a lot.

379
00:26:27,670 --> 00:26:29,755
We can't just leave it at that.

380
00:26:39,098 --> 00:26:40,182
You...

381
00:26:40,266 --> 00:26:42,601
What does your heart say?

382
00:26:44,854 --> 00:26:47,523
Have you forgiven me, Teo?

383
00:26:49,608 --> 00:26:52,361
Have you forgiven your mother?

384
00:26:59,243 --> 00:27:00,578
It's all in the past.

385
00:27:04,123 --> 00:27:05,791
What matters is the present.

386
00:27:08,627 --> 00:27:10,463
Thank you, son.

387
00:27:42,411 --> 00:27:45,664
I hope our departure goes smoothly.

388
00:27:49,543 --> 00:27:51,295
When we arrive in Vietnam,

389
00:27:52,338 --> 00:27:54,256
we'll be far away from the chaos here.

390
00:27:56,425 --> 00:27:58,677
But the conflict between my parents...

391
00:28:04,433 --> 00:28:06,435
Our journey will be long.

392
00:28:08,187 --> 00:28:12,983
We'll head to Palawan
and then cross the sea to Vietnam.

393
00:28:13,067 --> 00:28:17,071
When we get there,
we'll become new people.

394
00:28:18,739 --> 00:28:22,576
Maybe during the trip,
they'll finally talk it out.

395
00:28:23,035 --> 00:28:25,663
I hope that when we arrive,
our family will be whole.

396
00:28:26,163 --> 00:28:28,290
Don't worry about it now. Come on.

397
00:28:28,874 --> 00:28:30,292
Have you packed your stuff yet?

398
00:28:30,376 --> 00:28:31,627
Yeah, I'm good to go.

399
00:28:36,590 --> 00:28:37,925
What's wrong?

400
00:28:38,008 --> 00:28:39,927
There's a tip
that authorities and the Coast Guard

401
00:28:40,010 --> 00:28:42,263
will patrol the sea later.

402
00:28:43,389 --> 00:28:44,890
- What?
- The waters are rough.

403
00:28:44,974 --> 00:28:47,226
Because of that,
the boatman changed our schedule.

404
00:28:48,769 --> 00:28:51,355
W-what does that mean?
When are we leaving?

405
00:28:51,439 --> 00:28:52,690
Tonight.

406
00:28:53,899 --> 00:28:55,484
We need to tell Mama.

407
00:28:57,862 --> 00:28:58,904
Okay.

408
00:29:06,036 --> 00:29:07,246
Hello?

409
00:29:07,329 --> 00:29:08,497
Hello, Ronnie.

410
00:29:08,581 --> 00:29:10,666
Change of plans.
We're not leaving on Saturday.

411
00:29:10,749 --> 00:29:12,751
The boatman said
we'll leave at midnight.

412
00:29:13,377 --> 00:29:15,129
I'm ready anytime.

413
00:29:15,212 --> 00:29:16,964
All right, take care.

414
00:29:27,099 --> 00:29:28,350
Sir, it's Issay.

415
00:29:29,602 --> 00:29:30,853
Answer it, ma'am.

416
00:29:30,936 --> 00:29:35,483
Stay on the line as long as you can
until we trace it completely.

417
00:29:36,609 --> 00:29:38,527
Hello? Issay?

418
00:29:39,361 --> 00:29:40,946
Hello, Larajean?

419
00:29:42,156 --> 00:29:44,742
Hey, why are you crying?

420
00:29:45,284 --> 00:29:46,368
Larajean...

421
00:29:48,245 --> 00:29:50,331
they said we are going to leave now.

422
00:29:50,414 --> 00:29:53,000
<i>We're leaving everything behind.</i>

423
00:29:54,210 --> 00:29:57,046
I won't be able to get my books.

424
00:29:57,630 --> 00:29:59,381
Tracing, 20%.

425
00:29:59,465 --> 00:30:00,716
Uh...

426
00:30:00,799 --> 00:30:03,177
where are you guys going?

427
00:30:03,260 --> 00:30:07,723
Maybe... maybe I can bring your books
to you before you leave.

428
00:30:07,806 --> 00:30:10,809
Larajean, I don't know where we're going.

429
00:30:11,435 --> 00:30:13,395
And I don't know

430
00:30:13,479 --> 00:30:16,315
the exact address here.

431
00:30:16,398 --> 00:30:18,317
Hush now, hush now.

432
00:30:18,859 --> 00:30:21,862
I thought I'd finally be happy.

433
00:30:21,946 --> 00:30:24,657
I thought that when my family
was finally complete,

434
00:30:24,740 --> 00:30:27,159
everything would be fine.

435
00:30:28,369 --> 00:30:31,956
What do you mean your family is complete?

436
00:30:32,039 --> 00:30:33,207
Uh...

437
00:30:33,290 --> 00:30:34,500
Issay...

438
00:30:35,125 --> 00:30:37,086
isn't your mother dead?

439
00:30:37,169 --> 00:30:39,755
Larajean, no. No.

440
00:30:40,464 --> 00:30:43,300
<i>Sorry, I haven't told you.</i>

441
00:30:43,384 --> 00:30:46,845
<i>Mama is alive. She's alive.</i>

442
00:30:46,929 --> 00:30:48,931
She's with us now.

443
00:30:49,598 --> 00:30:51,934
I'm scared, Larajean.

444
00:30:52,017 --> 00:30:56,063
<i>I'm scared of the bad things</i>
<i>that could happen.</i>

445
00:30:56,146 --> 00:30:57,731
100%. Got it.

446
00:30:58,315 --> 00:31:00,317
Sir,

447
00:31:01,235 --> 00:31:03,153
there is a tower near the farm.

448
00:31:03,237 --> 00:31:04,863
It's within this perimeter.

449
00:31:05,614 --> 00:31:07,700
It's a farm lot in Barenas.

450
00:31:10,494 --> 00:31:13,539
Great. Let's tell Judge Divino
and Madam Katarina.

451
00:31:13,622 --> 00:31:14,456
No!

452
00:31:15,040 --> 00:31:16,667
I don't want them meddling.

453
00:31:16,750 --> 00:31:18,085
I can handle this.

454
00:31:22,298 --> 00:31:25,134
What's up with you?

455
00:31:26,051 --> 00:31:27,303
You don't trust me either?

456
00:31:30,347 --> 00:31:31,765
Of course I do.

457
00:31:32,266 --> 00:31:34,351
Come on now, I trust you.

458
00:31:45,654 --> 00:31:47,990
- Mr. Domeng.
- Sir?

459
00:31:49,074 --> 00:31:50,326
Sir, hold on.

460
00:31:50,993 --> 00:31:52,244
- Mr. Domeng.
- Sir?

461
00:31:54,288 --> 00:31:57,291
Don't forget to pick up
the boxes in the shop.

462
00:31:57,374 --> 00:31:58,792
The old displays, as well.

463
00:31:59,418 --> 00:32:01,587
Be careful with them,
we'll use them again.

464
00:32:01,670 --> 00:32:02,880
Yes, sir.

465
00:32:02,963 --> 00:32:04,048
Call me
once you've picked them up.

466
00:32:04,131 --> 00:32:05,132
Okay, sir.

467
00:33:03,857 --> 00:33:06,110
The airport, please. Domestic.

468
00:33:08,237 --> 00:33:09,697
Mister, stop!

469
00:33:09,780 --> 00:33:11,615
This isn't the way to the airport!

470
00:33:12,491 --> 00:33:15,911
I told you
there's no shortcut to the airport.

471
00:33:16,537 --> 00:33:18,288
I'm not gonna pay you.

472
00:33:24,628 --> 00:33:25,629
Hold up!

473
00:33:26,213 --> 00:33:28,298
Give me your bag! Give it to me!

474
00:33:28,757 --> 00:33:31,176
Give it to me, or else I'll kill you.

475
00:33:31,260 --> 00:33:32,511
Give it to me now!

476
00:33:35,806 --> 00:33:37,891
Now, take off your clothes!

477
00:33:37,975 --> 00:33:39,977
- What?
- Take them off! Yeah!

478
00:33:40,519 --> 00:33:41,854
Take your clothes off!

479
00:33:43,897 --> 00:33:45,190
Take your clothes off!

480
00:33:50,279 --> 00:33:52,322
Hey! That's my car!

481
00:33:53,866 --> 00:33:56,201
I'll get going.

482
00:34:03,959 --> 00:34:04,960
Raya.

483
00:34:11,300 --> 00:34:12,551
What's wrong?

484
00:34:28,859 --> 00:34:30,027
Ronnie.

485
00:34:32,237 --> 00:34:33,322
Raya?

486
00:34:33,864 --> 00:34:36,033
Ronnie, Raya isn't part of the plan.

487
00:34:36,116 --> 00:34:37,534
I know.

488
00:34:39,495 --> 00:34:40,913
Raya ran away from home.

489
00:34:41,497 --> 00:34:43,165
She almost got hurt.

490
00:34:43,248 --> 00:34:45,000
<i>I can't just leave her, Teo.</i>

491
00:34:45,501 --> 00:34:47,419
She can't come with us!
The Veronas might have sent her!

492
00:34:47,503 --> 00:34:49,421
Teo, Raya isn't like them! I know her.

493
00:34:49,505 --> 00:34:51,465
<i>How can you be sure?</i>

494
00:34:51,548 --> 00:34:52,800
<i>No, she can't come.</i>

495
00:34:52,883 --> 00:34:55,052
You're just adding more problems!

496
00:34:55,719 --> 00:34:57,346
<i>I understand.</i>

497
00:34:57,429 --> 00:34:59,765
But I'm sorry, guys.

498
00:35:00,849 --> 00:35:03,352
I can't just leave Raya like this.

499
00:35:03,435 --> 00:35:06,271
Ronnie, they'll
hunt you down, too, for sure!

500
00:35:06,355 --> 00:35:08,273
<i>I just need to make sure Raya is safe.</i>

501
00:35:08,357 --> 00:35:10,025
I'll catch up with you guys in...

502
00:35:10,442 --> 00:35:11,944
Vietnam? Wherever it is.

503
00:35:12,027 --> 00:35:13,153
Are you serious?

504
00:35:13,237 --> 00:35:15,739
Teo. It's Raya against all of us.

505
00:35:15,823 --> 00:35:17,991
If she snitches,
we can definitely handle it.

506
00:35:19,034 --> 00:35:22,788
Let's take Raya with us.
We can't leave Ronnie behind.

507
00:35:22,871 --> 00:35:24,790
Fine. Don't go in the house.

508
00:35:24,873 --> 00:35:26,625
<i>Wait for us outside. We're heading out.</i>

509
00:35:26,708 --> 00:35:30,254
You already know the plan, right?
Let's just meet there.

510
00:35:32,047 --> 00:35:34,299
Thank you, Teo. Thank you so much.

511
00:35:45,143 --> 00:35:46,645
Who are you texting?

512
00:35:47,020 --> 00:35:48,105
No one.

513
00:35:58,115 --> 00:36:00,367
Are you sure you didn't leave anything
in the bathroom?

514
00:36:00,826 --> 00:36:02,828
I checked it. It's all clean.

515
00:36:03,412 --> 00:36:04,663
- It's all good.
- Thanks.

516
00:36:04,746 --> 00:36:06,748
Please double-check the kitchen.

517
00:36:06,832 --> 00:36:09,084
Don't leave any trash.

518
00:36:09,167 --> 00:36:11,336
- Put it all in the trash can.
- Yes, Teo.

519
00:36:14,172 --> 00:36:15,257
Ma.

520
00:36:20,679 --> 00:36:21,930
Turn right.

521
00:36:29,605 --> 00:36:31,398
Hurry! Jepoy, come on!

522
00:36:31,481 --> 00:36:32,733
Get in the car now!

523
00:36:33,275 --> 00:36:34,610
Teo, let's go!

524
00:36:34,693 --> 00:36:35,694
Let's go!

525
00:36:36,862 --> 00:36:37,779
Come on!

526
00:36:43,035 --> 00:36:43,952
Ma?

527
00:36:44,036 --> 00:36:45,495
Someone's coming.

528
00:36:45,579 --> 00:36:47,372
I don't know who that is.
Jepoy, let's get out of here!

529
00:36:47,456 --> 00:36:48,916
- Come on!
- Get in the car!

530
00:36:48,999 --> 00:36:50,584
Get in the car! Let's go!

531
00:36:52,377 --> 00:36:54,129
Where's Mama and Issay?

532
00:36:54,212 --> 00:36:55,422
Where's Issay?

533
00:36:55,505 --> 00:36:57,215
Rita only causes trouble in this family!

534
00:36:57,299 --> 00:36:58,884
- I got it, Pa.
- Teo!

535
00:36:58,967 --> 00:37:00,177
Where's Issay? Issay!

536
00:37:00,260 --> 00:37:02,512
Ma! Ma!

537
00:37:02,596 --> 00:37:04,348
Ma, where are you going?

538
00:37:04,431 --> 00:37:05,891
Why are you running away?

539
00:37:05,974 --> 00:37:07,225
Why are you leaving us?

540
00:37:07,309 --> 00:37:10,020
Let me go, Issay! Just go back!

541
00:37:10,103 --> 00:37:11,563
Go with them!

542
00:37:11,647 --> 00:37:15,442
No, Ma! We'll leave together!
That's what you said, remember?

543
00:37:15,525 --> 00:37:18,236
Why do you want to be left behind?
Why are you running away?

544
00:37:18,320 --> 00:37:19,488
That's not true!

545
00:37:20,072 --> 00:37:21,823
Do you really think

546
00:37:22,824 --> 00:37:26,495
we'll all just be happy
now that you've found me?

547
00:37:26,995 --> 00:37:30,832
That days of being together would make up
for the years after I left you?

548
00:37:31,625 --> 00:37:33,335
- Issay!
- Teo, let's go!

549
00:37:33,418 --> 00:37:35,045
- Issay!
- We need to leave now!

550
00:37:35,128 --> 00:37:37,089
- Teo, where are you?
- Ma!

551
00:37:37,172 --> 00:37:38,674
- Issay!
- Issay!

552
00:37:38,757 --> 00:37:39,925
Ma...

553
00:37:40,467 --> 00:37:42,552
we'll do anything you want.

554
00:37:43,220 --> 00:37:44,638
Teo will make it happen.

555
00:37:45,806 --> 00:37:47,224
Teo?

556
00:37:47,307 --> 00:37:49,726
Teo won't be able to give me what I want!

557
00:37:49,810 --> 00:37:52,020
And certainly not your father!

558
00:37:52,980 --> 00:37:55,983
I'm so tired of being poor, Issay!

559
00:37:56,066 --> 00:37:58,402
I'm so sick of seeing your face

560
00:37:58,485 --> 00:38:02,239
because you remind me
how unfortunate I was!

561
00:38:05,033 --> 00:38:06,868
Don't follow me, understand?

562
00:38:07,828 --> 00:38:10,497
And don't ever call me Mama.

563
00:38:11,540 --> 00:38:15,544
The moment I left you,
I had forgotten I had children.

564
00:38:17,379 --> 00:38:19,006
Go with them!

565
00:38:42,279 --> 00:38:43,613
Issay!

566
00:38:43,697 --> 00:38:45,907
- Ma! Issay!
- Issay!

567
00:38:47,034 --> 00:38:49,661
- Issay. Issay!
- We have to go now!

568
00:38:49,745 --> 00:38:51,121
Pa, get in the car!

569
00:38:51,204 --> 00:38:52,330
- Issay!
- Hurry up!

570
00:38:52,414 --> 00:38:53,832
Get in the car.

571
00:39:02,340 --> 00:39:03,675
Turn right over there.

572
00:39:06,011 --> 00:39:07,387
I need to find the others!

573
00:39:07,471 --> 00:39:09,264
Let's meet up where Ronnie is.

574
00:39:09,347 --> 00:39:10,599
Hurry! Move! Take care!

575
00:39:32,454 --> 00:39:33,914
Split up!

576
00:39:33,997 --> 00:39:35,082
Move!

577
00:39:57,562 --> 00:39:59,815
- Who are you?
- Where are you going?

578
00:39:59,898 --> 00:40:00,982
Come with us!

579
00:40:01,066 --> 00:40:02,692
- Don't struggle!
- Who are you?

580
00:40:02,776 --> 00:40:05,612
Let me go! Help!

581
00:40:07,823 --> 00:40:09,825
Go over there. Look for him!

582
00:40:14,287 --> 00:40:15,956
Teo, show yourself!

583
00:40:18,583 --> 00:40:20,919
There's nowhere to escape!

584
00:40:54,244 --> 00:40:55,203
Hey!

585
00:40:55,287 --> 00:40:56,538
Stop right there!

586
00:40:56,621 --> 00:40:58,165
Stop moving!

587
00:40:58,832 --> 00:41:01,251
What now, huh?

588
00:41:02,586 --> 00:41:04,004
Thought you could escape?

589
00:41:25,442 --> 00:41:26,526
Teo!

590
00:41:27,110 --> 00:41:30,697
Teo! Teo!

591
00:41:32,449 --> 00:41:33,617
Come on.

592
00:41:35,827 --> 00:41:36,912
Hurry!

593
00:41:37,370 --> 00:41:38,538
Let's go!

594
00:41:45,462 --> 00:41:46,713
- Boss!
- Boss!

595
00:42:00,393 --> 00:42:02,145
Let go of me!

596
00:42:02,229 --> 00:42:04,147
- I said let me go!
- Issay?

597
00:42:04,231 --> 00:42:06,983
- I don't want to go with you!
- Issay! Issay!

598
00:42:07,067 --> 00:42:10,153
- Let go of me! Hey!
- Issay! Issay!

599
00:42:10,237 --> 00:42:11,988
I don't want to go with you!

600
00:42:12,489 --> 00:42:15,408
Let go of me! Get your hands off of me!

601
00:42:15,492 --> 00:42:17,869
- Open the door!
- Get off of me!

602
00:42:17,953 --> 00:42:19,913
- Issay!
- Get in!

603
00:42:19,996 --> 00:42:22,082
Let me go!

604
00:42:23,208 --> 00:42:27,545
Help! Somebody help me!

605
00:42:29,381 --> 00:42:30,507
Ace!

606
00:42:31,216 --> 00:42:32,676
- Sir!
- Ace! Ace!

607
00:42:35,470 --> 00:42:36,888
Bring him here!

608
00:42:36,972 --> 00:42:38,765
Quick! Get him in the car!

609
00:42:38,848 --> 00:42:40,517
Let's get him to the hospital! Quick!

610
00:42:44,980 --> 00:42:45,897
Ace!

611
00:42:48,984 --> 00:42:50,235
Help!

612
00:42:50,652 --> 00:42:52,737
Hurry!

613
00:42:52,821 --> 00:42:55,240
- Let's go! Ace?
- You bastards!

614
00:42:55,865 --> 00:42:58,118
I don't want to go with you!

615
00:42:58,201 --> 00:42:59,869
I don't want to!

616
00:43:01,204 --> 00:43:02,580
You bastards!

617
00:43:03,790 --> 00:43:05,709
I shot him in a bad spot.

618
00:43:06,209 --> 00:43:08,628
That demon ought to be dead.

619
00:43:08,712 --> 00:43:11,214
We have to find Issay.
Where is she?

620
00:43:11,298 --> 00:43:12,716
We don't have time!

621
00:43:15,010 --> 00:43:16,428
Please don't, sir!

622
00:43:16,511 --> 00:43:18,346
I'm not with them, sir!

623
00:43:18,430 --> 00:43:20,640
I saw a man badly injured.

624
00:43:20,724 --> 00:43:23,893
I saw a group of men
who took a young girl away!

625
00:43:24,394 --> 00:43:25,895
I'm just a humble farmer, sir!

626
00:43:25,979 --> 00:43:28,315
Please, sir! Have mercy!

627
00:43:31,234 --> 00:43:32,694
I'm not a bad person, sir!

628
00:43:39,993 --> 00:43:43,872
I thought Ma'am Raya
was in her room, but she isn't.

629
00:43:43,955 --> 00:43:46,458
I've called her,
but she's not answering.

630
00:43:46,541 --> 00:43:48,543
I just don't know where that child went.

631
00:43:48,960 --> 00:43:53,715
You know, I keep calling her,
but all my calls just go to voicemail.

632
00:43:54,215 --> 00:43:55,717
I called her friends!

633
00:43:55,800 --> 00:44:00,096
I asked if they know where she is,
but nobody has any idea where she is!

634
00:44:03,308 --> 00:44:06,186
- How about her bodyguard?
- I already called him.

635
00:44:06,269 --> 00:44:08,772
He went home right after
dropping Miss Raya off.

636
00:44:09,230 --> 00:44:10,482
He doesn't know anything.

637
00:44:11,024 --> 00:44:13,360
Call that boy. Teo's friend.

638
00:44:13,443 --> 00:44:14,694
- What?
- Just call him.

639
00:44:14,778 --> 00:44:16,446
I don't even know his number!

640
00:44:17,364 --> 00:44:19,449
O-okay, let me ask Larajean.

641
00:44:21,284 --> 00:44:23,203
Hello? Larajean?

642
00:44:23,286 --> 00:44:24,621
Madam!

643
00:44:24,704 --> 00:44:26,623
M-Madam Katarina!

644
00:44:26,706 --> 00:44:28,166
<i>Madam!</i>

645
00:44:28,249 --> 00:44:29,334
Hello?

646
00:44:29,417 --> 00:44:31,711
Ma'am, it's Ace... He...

647
00:44:31,795 --> 00:44:33,213
What's going on?

648
00:44:33,296 --> 00:44:35,048
Ma'am, it's Sir Ace.

649
00:44:35,465 --> 00:44:37,550
I told him that he--

650
00:44:37,634 --> 00:44:40,845
that he should tell you
everything about his plans,

651
00:44:40,929 --> 00:44:43,598
but he didn't listen to me...

652
00:44:43,681 --> 00:44:45,725
So, what happened?

653
00:44:45,809 --> 00:44:48,311
You've been going around in circles!

654
00:44:48,395 --> 00:44:51,272
Would you please
get a hold of yourself?

655
00:44:51,356 --> 00:44:52,357
What happened?

656
00:44:52,440 --> 00:44:54,192
Ace got shot!

657
00:44:54,275 --> 00:44:55,360
Oh, my gosh!

658
00:44:55,443 --> 00:44:56,694
Where is he?

659
00:45:07,580 --> 00:45:08,706
Basin.

660
00:45:15,338 --> 00:45:16,673
We're losing him.

661
00:45:16,756 --> 00:45:18,133
Everyone's clear, I am clear.

662
00:45:18,216 --> 00:45:19,926
No pulse.

663
00:45:42,866 --> 00:45:44,534
This has been abandoned
for a long time now.

664
00:45:45,743 --> 00:45:48,079
We'll be staying here in the meantime.

665
00:45:48,663 --> 00:45:49,914
You're right.

666
00:45:50,540 --> 00:45:52,459
We shouldn't go out too much.

667
00:45:52,917 --> 00:45:56,004
I'm certain that if the police see us,
it's jail time.

668
00:45:56,880 --> 00:45:59,466
Plus, even if we're sure
that Ace took Issay away,

669
00:45:59,549 --> 00:46:02,385
the police won't believe us
if we don't have any proof.

670
00:46:03,052 --> 00:46:04,220
So?

671
00:46:04,888 --> 00:46:06,723
We're just gonna hide here and do nothing?

672
00:46:06,806 --> 00:46:08,600
We're not hiding.

673
00:46:08,683 --> 00:46:11,227
We'll think of a good plan
before striking.

674
00:46:12,896 --> 00:46:15,064
We'll get Issay back from the Veronas.

675
00:46:15,148 --> 00:46:18,234
Well, yes, and the easiest way to do that

676
00:46:18,318 --> 00:46:22,113
is to return this dead weight
back to the Veronas.

677
00:46:22,197 --> 00:46:23,072
Pa...

678
00:46:25,658 --> 00:46:26,576
It's true!

679
00:46:27,702 --> 00:46:30,497
Let's give Raya back. Let's give Gem back.

680
00:46:30,580 --> 00:46:32,415
Then they'll leave us alone.

681
00:46:32,499 --> 00:46:34,042
Throw your mother in, too.

682
00:46:34,125 --> 00:46:35,877
The judge could be waiting for her.

683
00:46:35,960 --> 00:46:38,129
Why are you the one
deciding things for me?

684
00:46:39,047 --> 00:46:42,133
I'll leave when I want,
not when you say I should.

685
00:46:42,217 --> 00:46:44,636
That's how you've always been.

686
00:46:44,719 --> 00:46:47,055
Even when you left before, right?

687
00:46:47,138 --> 00:46:48,598
You left even when we didn't want you to.

688
00:46:48,681 --> 00:46:49,599
Dad, Mom!

689
00:46:49,682 --> 00:46:50,934
Come on!

690
00:46:52,435 --> 00:46:53,853
Didn't we say
we'd get through this together?

691
00:46:53,937 --> 00:46:54,979
No one gets left behind.

692
00:46:55,063 --> 00:46:58,107
Just wait.
We'll go our separate ways soon.

693
00:46:58,650 --> 00:47:00,652
Especially when we're backed
into a corner.

694
00:47:01,361 --> 00:47:03,947
Teo, just get rid of those people!

695
00:47:04,030 --> 00:47:06,866
That way,
we'll be able to move more freely!

696
00:47:06,950 --> 00:47:08,201
No, Pa.

697
00:47:09,160 --> 00:47:10,411
Never.

698
00:47:11,579 --> 00:47:14,082
And please, can you set aside
your grievances for now?

699
00:47:14,165 --> 00:47:17,502
We should all worry about Issay right now.
We have to get her back from the Veronas.

700
00:48:09,429 --> 00:48:13,057
Please let me go! I don't want to be here!

701
00:48:13,141 --> 00:48:14,642
Be strong, Ace.

702
00:48:15,143 --> 00:48:16,227
You're a Verona.

703
00:48:18,146 --> 00:48:19,564
Stop crying!

704
00:48:21,024 --> 00:48:22,775
Fifty million, Judge Verona.

705
00:48:22,859 --> 00:48:25,236
If not,
your son's corpse will welcome you.

706
00:48:25,737 --> 00:48:26,779
No!

707
00:48:26,863 --> 00:48:29,949
I won't just give you
what you bastards want.

708
00:48:30,533 --> 00:48:33,536
I'll get my son back
without giving you anything.

709
00:48:36,706 --> 00:48:38,708
Your father is fearless, isn't he?

710
00:48:42,670 --> 00:48:44,088
No!

711
00:48:44,172 --> 00:48:46,299
- Give me your hand.
- No!

712
00:48:46,382 --> 00:48:48,801
Stop crying!

713
00:48:51,012 --> 00:48:52,055
Huh?

714
00:48:52,138 --> 00:48:55,558
Ace? Ace! Nurse! Nurse!

715
00:48:57,226 --> 00:48:58,478
Excuse me, ma'am.

716
00:49:05,777 --> 00:49:07,278
Doc, it's Patient Verona!

717
00:49:07,362 --> 00:49:09,781
- He's having a seizure.
- Yes, yes.

718
00:49:15,078 --> 00:49:16,496
Um, excuse me, ma'am.

719
00:49:42,480 --> 00:49:45,400
Go ahead.
Or it'll keep bothering you.

720
00:49:54,075 --> 00:49:55,118
Miss Raya.

721
00:49:55,660 --> 00:49:56,661
Miss Raya.

722
00:49:56,744 --> 00:49:58,162
<i>Miss Raya, I know you're listening.</i>

723
00:49:58,246 --> 00:49:59,831
Your brother got shot.

724
00:49:59,914 --> 00:50:02,500
He's currently in critical condition
at the hospital.

725
00:50:02,583 --> 00:50:03,876
<i>The investigation is ongoing.</i>

726
00:50:03,960 --> 00:50:06,295
They found out who shot him.

727
00:50:07,213 --> 00:50:08,214
It was Teo.

728
00:50:13,386 --> 00:50:14,971
Did you shoot my brother?

729
00:50:17,181 --> 00:50:18,850
He's critical.

730
00:50:18,933 --> 00:50:20,893
My brother is on the verge of death.

731
00:50:20,977 --> 00:50:22,311
What, are you happy now?

732
00:50:23,855 --> 00:50:25,273
Wait a minute, Raya.

733
00:50:26,315 --> 00:50:28,735
Before you jump to conclusions,
you should--

734
00:50:28,818 --> 00:50:30,486
What else do you need to say?

735
00:50:30,570 --> 00:50:32,071
He is in danger!

736
00:50:32,488 --> 00:50:34,657
What if something bad happens to him?

737
00:50:35,324 --> 00:50:36,993
I need to go.

738
00:50:37,410 --> 00:50:39,829
- Raya.
- Of course you will stop me!

739
00:50:40,788 --> 00:50:42,790
You never cared about my brother.

740
00:50:42,874 --> 00:50:44,041
Never!

741
00:50:47,086 --> 00:50:49,088
I don't even know what I'm doing here.

742
00:50:49,172 --> 00:50:51,215
I don't even know what's going on.

743
00:50:52,216 --> 00:50:54,761
My brother is fighting for his life,
and yet...

744
00:50:54,844 --> 00:50:57,263
and yet I'm here! Why?

745
00:50:59,557 --> 00:51:01,225
I need to leave.

746
00:51:03,269 --> 00:51:04,270
Raya.

747
00:51:04,937 --> 00:51:06,272
Raya, wait a minute.

748
00:51:09,233 --> 00:51:11,068
Raya.

749
00:51:14,071 --> 00:51:15,740
I don't get you at all.

750
00:51:15,823 --> 00:51:18,493
Let me remind you,
you were the one who left, Raya.

751
00:51:18,576 --> 00:51:20,745
I asked them for a favor. And now what?

752
00:51:21,579 --> 00:51:23,206
You'll just leave us behind?

753
00:51:23,289 --> 00:51:24,624
You really are a brat.

754
00:51:24,707 --> 00:51:26,542
I'm not being a brat!

755
00:51:26,959 --> 00:51:28,503
What I said was true!

756
00:51:28,586 --> 00:51:31,047
Gem and Pearl?

757
00:51:31,130 --> 00:51:32,882
They're all traitors!

758
00:51:34,759 --> 00:51:36,177
If you were me,

759
00:51:36,260 --> 00:51:38,513
- would you still stay?
- Yes!

760
00:51:40,181 --> 00:51:43,351
Because I know the truth
about why everything is happening!

761
00:51:43,893 --> 00:51:47,146
Fine. Gem and Pearl?

762
00:51:47,563 --> 00:51:49,565
This is all their fault.

763
00:51:49,649 --> 00:51:51,067
And your family?

764
00:51:51,609 --> 00:51:54,612
Fine, they're the poor victims.
Is that it?

765
00:51:57,573 --> 00:52:00,493
All I know is that I need to go back home
to my family!

766
00:52:00,576 --> 00:52:01,577
Fine.

767
00:52:02,119 --> 00:52:03,788
Go ahead, Raya.

768
00:52:03,871 --> 00:52:06,207
If that's what you believe in,
I won't stop you.

769
00:52:06,290 --> 00:52:08,376
Do what you think is right.

770
00:52:08,459 --> 00:52:10,211
But before you leave, I need your word

771
00:52:10,294 --> 00:52:13,631
that you won't rat us out, no matter what.

772
00:52:13,714 --> 00:52:16,634
That you'll never tell them
about our plan.

773
00:52:17,343 --> 00:52:18,678
Because if you do...

774
00:52:20,471 --> 00:52:23,558
then you'll be a traitor just like them.

775
00:52:24,475 --> 00:52:26,477
They ruined your family, didn't they?

776
00:52:27,603 --> 00:52:29,272
They ruined your life.

777
00:52:31,983 --> 00:52:34,902
Have you ever wondered
how your family ruined their lives?

778
00:52:37,196 --> 00:52:38,531
It goes both ways, Raya.

779
00:52:39,991 --> 00:52:41,826
In life, everything is a two-way street.

780
00:52:42,869 --> 00:52:44,620
I don't want to go back home.

781
00:52:46,122 --> 00:52:48,708
But I can't be here.

782
00:52:51,752 --> 00:52:54,714
Thank you so much for your help, Ronnie.

783
00:52:57,091 --> 00:52:59,427
You've been so good to me.

784
00:53:01,095 --> 00:53:02,847
I won't forget that.

785
00:53:17,403 --> 00:53:18,988
What the hell are you doing?

786
00:53:19,071 --> 00:53:20,489
- What's this?
- What's this?

787
00:53:21,073 --> 00:53:23,075
I shot your brother, Raya.

788
00:53:24,327 --> 00:53:26,579
And if it happened again,
I'd do it all over again.

789
00:53:26,662 --> 00:53:28,664
I just defended myself.

790
00:53:29,123 --> 00:53:31,751
Because a family is waiting
for me to come home.

791
00:53:32,501 --> 00:53:36,005
Our lives and our futures
are at stake here.

792
00:53:36,088 --> 00:53:37,965
Let me go!

793
00:53:39,675 --> 00:53:41,552
You're holding me here against my will!

794
00:53:41,636 --> 00:53:42,720
This is kidnapping!

795
00:53:42,803 --> 00:53:44,305
Raya, we're cornered!

796
00:53:44,388 --> 00:53:45,640
You're making it even worse for us.

797
00:53:45,723 --> 00:53:46,891
What the hell do you want?

798
00:53:46,974 --> 00:53:49,810
For your brother to kill us?
For your dad to kill us?

799
00:53:51,520 --> 00:53:53,522
Don't take this personally.

800
00:53:53,606 --> 00:53:56,484
You won't get hurt if you just cooperate.

801
00:53:58,361 --> 00:53:59,445
You have a point, too.

802
00:54:00,279 --> 00:54:02,531
You should be with your family now.

803
00:54:02,615 --> 00:54:04,450
Not with the enemy.

804
00:54:05,034 --> 00:54:07,870
So once Issay is returned to us,
you'll be able to go home too.

805
00:54:10,539 --> 00:54:11,958
Your phones.

806
00:54:13,042 --> 00:54:13,876
Mine too?

807
00:54:13,960 --> 00:54:15,836
Just for now, Ronnie.

808
00:54:15,920 --> 00:54:18,422
We're desperate.
We're doing this for our family.

809
00:54:24,261 --> 00:54:25,346
Yours too.

810
00:54:25,888 --> 00:54:27,348
It's on the table.

811
00:54:53,165 --> 00:54:54,417
Here.

812
00:54:54,500 --> 00:54:55,751
Drink.

813
00:55:06,262 --> 00:55:08,472
Do you think
you can still go back to your family?

814
00:55:10,182 --> 00:55:13,436
We'll make sure to kill them all.

815
00:55:13,811 --> 00:55:16,063
We're going to destroy all the Crisantos.

816
00:55:16,147 --> 00:55:20,026
You monsters!

817
00:55:20,109 --> 00:55:23,029
Why would you do that to my family?

818
00:55:23,112 --> 00:55:25,448
You're all monsters!

819
00:55:25,531 --> 00:55:27,450
You monsters!

820
00:55:27,533 --> 00:55:30,119
You're all evil!

821
00:55:30,202 --> 00:55:31,787
Demons!

822
00:55:32,329 --> 00:55:33,748
- Come here.
- Demons!

823
00:55:33,831 --> 00:55:36,292
Teo will save me!

824
00:55:36,375 --> 00:55:37,710
Let me go!

825
00:55:37,793 --> 00:55:39,253
- Sit!
- It hurts!

826
00:55:39,336 --> 00:55:40,880
- I said sit down! Hold her!
- No!

827
00:55:41,881 --> 00:55:43,382
Let me go!

828
00:55:43,466 --> 00:55:45,051
I said let me go!

829
00:55:45,134 --> 00:55:47,219
What are you doing? Don't! Please!

830
00:55:47,303 --> 00:55:49,597
Please! Don't!

831
00:55:49,680 --> 00:55:51,474
I'm begging you!

832
00:55:57,438 --> 00:55:59,523
If they lay a finger on my sister...

833
00:56:00,608 --> 00:56:03,235
may God have mercy,
but I'll finish them off one by one.

834
00:56:09,492 --> 00:56:11,619
We'll find Issay.

835
00:56:11,702 --> 00:56:13,370
We'll bring her back home.

836
00:56:13,954 --> 00:56:16,624
We'll work together, Teo.
I'll be right by your side.

837
00:56:52,827 --> 00:56:55,246
Raya. Raya.

838
00:56:57,331 --> 00:56:58,666
No way!

839
00:57:02,336 --> 00:57:04,338
Let me go.

840
00:57:24,650 --> 00:57:25,734
Raya.

841
00:57:26,819 --> 00:57:28,487
Or should I say, Teo?

842
00:57:29,155 --> 00:57:30,072
Or Gem?

843
00:57:30,156 --> 00:57:32,449
Your son, Ace, took my sister.

844
00:57:32,533 --> 00:57:36,370
Not once did I yield
in negotiations like this.

845
00:57:36,912 --> 00:57:39,331
You don't call the shots here, Teo.

846
00:57:40,791 --> 00:57:43,043
Hello? Hello?

847
00:57:55,222 --> 00:57:56,390
<i>Hold her!</i>

848
00:57:56,473 --> 00:57:58,601
<i>- Let me go!</i>
- Issay?

849
00:57:58,684 --> 00:57:59,643
- <i>No!</i>
- Issay?

850
00:57:59,727 --> 00:58:02,605
<i>Don't! Please, don't!</i>

851
00:58:02,688 --> 00:58:04,565
I'm begging you, please!

852
00:58:04,648 --> 00:58:07,026
No! Issay!

853
00:58:08,194 --> 00:58:10,779
- You monsters.
- What's going on?

854
00:58:10,863 --> 00:58:12,031
Teo?

855
00:58:17,494 --> 00:58:19,246
You're a monster, Divino!

856
00:58:19,330 --> 00:58:21,916
Finally, you've realized
who you're dealing with.

857
00:58:21,999 --> 00:58:23,584
<i>This is what will happen.</i>

858
00:58:23,667 --> 00:58:25,502
<i>I'll return Issay to you.</i>

859
00:58:25,586 --> 00:58:27,838
Then you'll return Raya to me.

860
00:58:27,922 --> 00:58:29,673
In one piece.

861
00:58:30,216 --> 00:58:31,717
<i> No bargaining.</i>

862
00:58:31,800 --> 00:58:33,469
No cheating.

863
00:58:34,803 --> 00:58:37,640
Wait for my next call
to know when we'll meet up.

864
00:58:52,571 --> 00:58:53,906
So many people have gotten hurt.

865
00:58:53,989 --> 00:58:55,824
My conscience can't take it anymore!

866
00:58:56,867 --> 00:58:58,786
Let's meet at the old cafe in Baltazar.

867
00:58:58,869 --> 00:59:01,080
<i>You'll be getting back</i>
<i>your sister's corpse.</i>

868
00:59:01,163 --> 00:59:02,998
I've done far worse things than you know!

869
00:59:03,082 --> 00:59:04,583
<i>I'll kill her!</i>

870
00:59:04,667 --> 00:59:05,542
Damn that woman!

871
00:59:06,752 --> 00:59:10,172
<i>Before we escape,</i>
<i>we should at least weaken them.</i>

872
00:59:10,256 --> 00:59:13,926
<i>If we weaken them,</i>
<i>they can't stop us, wherever we go.</i>

873
00:59:15,302 --> 00:59:17,346
<i>Teo! What are you doing here?</i>
